name: High Plank
description: The standard plank performed on hands rather than forearms, maintaining a rigid straight line from head to heels. This fundamental position builds anti-extension strength and is the starting position for many exercises.
instructions: Start in push-up position, hands directly under shoulders
Extend legs behind with feet hip-width apart
Form straight line from head to heels
Engage core by drawing navel toward spine
Hold position while breathing steadily
formCues: Don't let hips sag or pike

name: Forearm Plank
description: The foundational core stability exercise performed on forearms and toes, maintaining a rigid straight line from head to heels. This isometric hold builds anti-extension strength and core endurance.
instructions: Start face down, place forearms on floor with elbows under shoulders
Lift body onto forearms and toes, forming straight line
Engage core by drawing navel toward spine
Keep hips level, don't let them sag or pike up
Hold position while breathing steadily

name: Side Plank
description: A lateral core stability exercise performed on one forearm, targeting the obliques and lateral stabilizers. This anti-lateral flexion hold builds frontal plane stability essential for athletic performance.
instructions: Lie on side with forearm on floor, elbow under shoulder
Stack feet or stagger them for balance
Lift hips off floor, creating straight line from head to feet
Keep top hip stacked directly over bottom hip
Hold position, then switch sides

name: Dead Bug
description: A supine core stability exercise extending opposite arm and leg while maintaining a flat lower back. This anti-extension movement is exceptionally safe for those with back issues while building deep core control.
instructions: Lie on back with arms extended toward ceiling
Lift legs to 90 degrees at hips and knees (tabletop)
Press lower back firmly into floor
Slowly extend opposite arm and leg while maintaining back contact
Return to start, alternate sides
formCues: Lower back stays flat on floor

name: Ab Wheel Rollout
description: An anti-extension exercise rolling an ab wheel forward while resisting spinal extension. Start from knees and progress to standing variation. This challenging movement builds exceptional anterior core strength and control.
instructions: Kneel on mat (or stand for advanced), grip ab wheel handles
Brace core and maintain neutral spine
Roll wheel forward, extending body toward floor
Go as far as you can control without back arching
Pull wheel back using core, not hip flexors

name: Body Saw
description: A dynamic plank variation using sliders to move the body forward and backward while maintaining rigid core position. This anti-extension exercise progressively increases lever arm and challenge.
instructions: Start in forearm plank with feet on sliders or towels
Maintain rigid plank position throughout
Push body backward by pressing forearms into floor
Slide until arms are more extended, increasing difficulty
Pull body forward to return, keeping core braced

name: Hollow Body Hold
description: A gymnastics-derived core exercise holding a curved hollow position with arms overhead and legs extended. This anti-extension hold develops the total anterior chain tension essential for advanced movements.
instructions: Lie on back with arms extended overhead
Press lower back firmly into floor
Lift shoulders and legs off floor simultaneously
Form a slight banana or hollow shape
Hold position while maintaining lower back contact

name: Long Lever Plank
description: An advanced plank variation with arms extended further forward, increasing the lever arm and dramatically increasing core demand. This progression builds toward harder anti-extension exercises.
instructions: Start in forearm plank position
Walk forearms forward 4-6 inches ahead of shoulders
Maintain rigid straight line from head to heels
Brace core maximally to resist extension
Hold position with increased lever arm

name: Weighted Plank
description: A loaded plank variation with weight placed on the back to increase resistance. This progression adds external load to the standard plank for continued strength development.
instructions: Set up in forearm plank position
Have partner place weight plate on upper back
Alternatively use weighted vest
Maintain rigid plank position with added load
Hold for prescribed time

name: Stir the Pot
description: A dynamic stability ball plank making small circular motions with the forearms, challenging anti-extension and anti-rotation simultaneously. This exercise builds exceptional reflexive core stability.
instructions: Place forearms on stability ball, feet on floor in plank
Maintain rigid plank position throughout
Make small circles with forearms, stirring the ball
Circle clockwise for prescribed reps
Reverse direction and repeat

name: Pallof Press
description: An anti-rotation exercise pressing a cable or band handle away from the body while resisting rotational forces. This functional movement builds rotational stability essential for sports and daily activities.
instructions: Stand perpendicular to cable machine, grab handle at chest
Step away to create tension, feet shoulder-width apart
Hold handle at chest with both hands
Press handle straight out from chest
Hold extended position, resist rotation, then return

name: Bird Dog
description: A fundamental anti-rotation and anti-extension exercise extending opposite arm and leg from a quadruped position. This safe movement builds core stability and is excellent for back health and rehab.
instructions: Start on hands and knees, hands under shoulders, knees under hips
Brace core and maintain neutral spine
Extend right arm forward and left leg back simultaneously
Keep hips and shoulders level, don't rotate
Return to start, repeat on opposite side

name: Single-Arm Farmer Carry
description: A unilateral loaded carry holding weight on one side while walking, forcing the core to resist lateral flexion. This functional anti-lateral flexion exercise builds real-world core stability and grip strength.
instructions: Hold heavy dumbbell or kettlebell in one hand
Stand tall, shoulders level despite uneven load
Walk forward with controlled steps
Resist leaning toward or away from weight
Complete distance then switch hands

name: Renegade Row
description: A combination plank and row exercise alternating rowing dumbbells while maintaining a rigid plank position. This anti-rotation movement challenges core stability under dynamic loading.
instructions: Start in high plank with hands on dumbbells, feet wide
Maintain rigid plank position throughout
Row one dumbbell to hip while pressing other into floor
Lower with control, keeping hips square
Alternate sides with each rep

name: Plank with Shoulder Tap
description: A dynamic plank variation tapping each shoulder alternately while resisting hip rotation. This anti-rotation exercise progresses the basic plank by adding movement and instability.
instructions: Start in high plank position, hands under shoulders
Feet wider than hip-width for stability
Lift one hand to tap opposite shoulder
Keep hips square, don't rotate
Return hand, alternate sides

name: Anti-Rotation Press
description: A half-kneeling anti-rotation exercise pressing weight or cable away from the body while resisting rotational forces. This position emphasizes hip and core stability in a split stance commonly used in sports.
instructions: Kneel in half-kneeling position perpendicular to cable or band anchor
Inside knee down, outside foot planted
Hold handle at chest with both hands
Press straight out while resisting rotation
Hold extended position, return with control, then switch sides

name: Crunch
description: The classic abdominal flexion exercise curling the upper spine off the floor to contract the rectus abdominis. This isolation movement targets the upper abs through a short range of motion.
instructions: Lie on back with knees bent, feet flat on floor
Place hands behind head or across chest
Contract abs to curl shoulders off floor
Lift shoulder blades, keeping lower back on floor
Lower with control to starting position

name: Bicycle Crunch
description: A dynamic crunch alternating elbow to opposite knee in a cycling motion, targeting both rectus abdominis and obliques. This combined flexion and rotation movement provides comprehensive ab training.
instructions: Lie on back, hands behind head, legs lifted
Bring right elbow toward left knee while extending right leg
Rotate through the movement, engaging obliques
Switch sides in continuous cycling motion
Keep shoulder blades off floor throughout

name: Reverse Crunch
description: An abdominal flexion exercise lifting the hips and pelvis toward the ribcage rather than curling the upper body down. This lower-ab emphasis variation builds strength through hip flexion with spinal flexion.
instructions: Lie on back with arms at sides, palms down
Lift legs to 90 degrees at hips and knees
Contract lower abs to curl pelvis toward chest
Lift hips off floor, bringing knees toward face
Lower with control to starting position

name: Hanging Leg Raise
description: An advanced abdominal flexion exercise raising legs while hanging from a bar, challenging grip and abs simultaneously. This exercise provides intense lower ab activation through a large range of motion.
instructions: Hang from pull-up bar with overhand grip
Start with legs straight, body in dead hang
Contract abs to lift legs toward bar
Raise until legs parallel to floor or higher
Lower with control to full extension

name: Lying Leg Raise
description: An abdominal flexion exercise raising straight legs while lying on the floor. This exercise emphasizes the lower abdominals and hip flexors through controlled hip flexion.
instructions: Lie flat on back, legs straight, hands under hips for support
Keep lower back pressed into floor
Raise straight legs until perpendicular to floor
Lower legs slowly, keeping them straight
Stop just before feet touch floor and repeat

name: V-Up
description: A full-body abdominal exercise simultaneously lifting torso and legs to touch hands to feet in a V position. This challenging flexion movement requires significant core strength and coordination.
instructions: Lie flat on back with arms extended overhead
Keep legs straight, press lower back into floor
Simultaneously lift upper body and legs
Reach hands toward feet at top, forming V shape
Lower with control to starting position

name: Toe Touch
description: A crunch variation reaching straight up to touch toes with legs extended vertically. This upper ab focused movement provides a good range of motion for abdominal flexion.
instructions: Lie on back with legs extended straight up toward ceiling
Arms extended toward ceiling as well
Crunch up, reaching hands toward toes
Lift shoulder blades off floor, touch or reach for toes
Lower with control to starting position

name: Cable Crunch
description: A weighted abdominal flexion exercise kneeling before a cable and crunching downward against resistance. This loaded movement allows progressive overload for ab strength and hypertrophy.
instructions: Kneel facing cable machine, rope attachment overhead
Hold rope behind head or at sides of face
Crunch down, bringing elbows toward knees
Focus on spinal flexion, not hip flexion
Return to starting position with control

name: Russian Twist
description: A seated rotational core exercise twisting side to side with or without weight. This classic rotation movement targets the obliques through loaded spinal rotation.
instructions: Sit with knees bent, lean back to engage core
Lift feet off floor slightly, or keep planted for easier version
Hold weight at chest or clasp hands together
Rotate torso to one side, touching weight to floor
Rotate to other side, alternating continuously
formCues: Touch weight to floor each side
Feet can be up or down

name: Cable Woodchop
description: A rotational core exercise pulling a cable diagonally across the body from high to low or low to high. This functional movement trains the diagonal sling patterns used in athletics and daily life.
instructions: Stand perpendicular to cable machine, cable at high or low position
Grip handle with both hands, arms extended
Rotate torso, pulling cable diagonally across body
Keep arms relatively straight, rotate through hips and core
Return with control, complete reps then switch sides

name: Medicine Ball Woodchop
description: An explosive rotational exercise swinging a medicine ball diagonally across the body. This power-focused movement develops rotational power for sports while building core strength.
instructions: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, hold medicine ball
Start with ball at one hip or above shoulder
Rotate explosively, swinging ball diagonally across body
Pivot on feet to allow full hip rotation
Control the deceleration, return and repeat, then switch directions

name: Landmine Rotation
description: A standing rotational exercise swinging a barbell anchored at one end from side to side. This unique setup provides smooth resistance for rotational power development.
instructions: Set barbell in landmine attachment or corner
Stand facing barbell end, grip with both hands extended
Rotate torso, sweeping bar in arc from side to side
Pivot on feet to allow full hip rotation
Control throughout the full range of motion

name: Windshield Wiper
description: An advanced rotational exercise sweeping legs side to side while hanging or lying. This challenging movement requires significant oblique strength and control through a large rotational range.
instructions: Lie on back with arms out to sides, or hang from bar
Raise legs to vertical (lying) or horizontal (hanging)
Lower legs to one side while keeping shoulders flat
Sweep legs to other side in controlled arc
Continue alternating like windshield wipers

name: Medicine Ball Slam
description: An explosive full-body exercise slamming a medicine ball into the ground with maximal force. This power movement develops core power, coordination, and serves as excellent conditioning.
instructions: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart holding medicine ball
Raise ball overhead, extending onto toes
Slam ball into ground with maximum force
Use entire body, hinging at hips and engaging core
Catch ball on bounce and repeat immediately
